# Answer-of-javaScript-Exercice
Algorithm Challenges in js

Write a JavaScript function to get the number of days in a month.


function getDaysInMonth(date){

let d= new Date(date);
let dayofMonth= new Date(d.getFullYear(), d.getMonth()+1,0);
return dayofMonth.getDate();
}

console.log(getDaysInMonth(1, 2012));

//getMonth() return an integer number between 0 and 11 adding 1 will return the integer between 1 and 12
//0 any missing fields are given the lowest possible value (1 for day, 0 for every other component)



